# Waby — Project Overview

Waby is a **smart baby car seat safety system** built as a final-year project (solo developer, ~2-week build deadline — prioritise working functionality over visual polish). It monitors an infant in a car seat and sends escalating alerts to prevent child endangerment.

## Stack
- **App:** Flutter (Dart, null-safe).
- **Firmware:** ESP32 (Arduino / C++).
- **Backend / API / database:** Firebase Realtime Database (free Spark plan).
- **Data flow:** ESP32 → WiFi → Firebase; the Flutter app reads live data from Firebase. (Bluetooth appears in the UI but Firebase carries the real data.)

## Hardware sensors
FSR (presence/weight), auto-detect buckle, DHT11 (temperature), GPS NEO-6M, ESP32. Outputs: LED indicators + buzzer for alarms.

## Firebase structure
- `seatcare/live/` — current sensor readings (temperature, presence, buckled, distance, status).
- `seatcare/contacts/` — next-of-kin records (this is the CRUD feature: add / edit / delete).
- `seatcare/logs/` — one entry per alarm event (used as the "real detection data" test evidence).

## Alert logic (authoritative — do not silence danger cases)
- No weight → idle, no alarms.
- Weight + NOT buckled + caregiver near → **buckle reminder** (gentle).
- Weight + caregiver FAR → **left-behind alarm**, regardless of buckle state.
- Weight + temperature over threshold → **heat alarm**.
- Escalation: L1 phone notification → L2 loud on-device alarm → L3 notify next-of-kin with GPS.

## Conventions
- Folder structure: `core/`, `models/`, `screens/`, `services/`, `widgets/`.
- Use `StreamBuilder` for live Firebase data.
- All colours/fonts come from `lib/core/theme.dart` — never hard-code colours in widgets.
- Keep business logic in `services/`, not in widgets.
- The app is being renamed from "SeatCare" to **Waby** — use Waby in all user-facing text.
